# NurseAda Integration Consistency

## Gateway → Backend Calls

- Use `httpx.AsyncClient()` with timeout (8–15s).
- Check `if not GATEWAY_*_URL` before calling; provide fallback when unset.
- On network error: allow through or return helpful message—never block users.
- Always `.rstrip('/')` on base URL before appending path.

## API Contracts

| Service | Endpoint | Request | Response |
|---------|----------|---------|----------|
| CDSS | POST /triage | `{query, context}` | `{severity, suggestions, inferred_codes, confidence, reasoning}` |
| CDSS | POST /code-check | `{agent_id, query, context}` | `{ok, reason, resolved_codes, agent_id}` |
| CDSS | POST /drug-interactions | `{query, patient_id?}` | `{interactions, warnings, codes_checked}` |
| Knowledge | POST /retrieve | `{query, top_k}` | `{chunks: [{text, source}], sources}` |
| XAI | POST /visualize/saliency | `{image_url?, features?}` | `{type, ...}` (saliency_radiology or saliency_tabular) |
| Knowledge | POST /retrieve/herbal | `{query, top_k}` | `{chunks: [{text, source, condition}], sources}` |

## Patient Data

- Gateway GET `/patient/{id}` proxies to FHIR `GET /Patient/{id}`.
- Chat request accepts `patient_id`; passed to agent context.

## New Integrations

- Add URL to `config.py` and `.env.example`.
- Implement fallback when service unavailable.
- Document request/response in this rule or service README.
